  <scopecontent id="aspace_5919d2c0f448d86a94009a553e018215">
    <head>COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
<p>Petitions to Congress from inhabitants of Tompkins County concerning abolition of slavery in Washington, DC, the annexation of Texas, and other anti-slavery issues, 1836-1845; tax schedules, and photocopies of articles from the <title>Ithaca Chronicle</title>, <title>Ithaca Journal</title>, <title>Trumansburg Advertiser</title>, and <title>The Flag</title>, containing speeches, letters, essays, election results and reports of anti-slavery and Free Soil meetings.</p>  </scopecontent>
  <prefercite id="aspace_49e73312e3c4f367c7b2b23e11f2389b">
